  "prompt": "How much of demonetized money, might not come back to the banking system?",
  "response": "The question about how much demonetized money might not return to the banking system is likely referring to events such as the demonetization of certain currency notes in India in 2016. During that event, the Indian government demonetized the 500 and 1,000 rupee notes to curb black money, counterfeit currency, and corruption. \n\nInitially, there was speculation that a significant portion of the demonetized currency would not return to the banking system, as it was believed to be held as black money. However, according to the Reserve Bank of India's annual report for the fiscal year 2017-18, about 99.3% of the demonetized currency was returned to the banking system. This indicated that only a small fraction of the demonetized notes did not come back.\n\nIf you are referring to a different or more recent demonetization event, please provide more details so I can give a more specific answer.",
